### Commit message format
- **Subject**: ≤72 chars, Imperative, Capitalized, no period
- **Blank line** after subject
- **Body**: explain what/why, wrap at 72 chars; bullets ok
- Should complete: “If applied, this commit will <subject>”

### References
- Header: "[#123] …" or "CAT-123 …"
- Body: "Fixes #123" (auto-links on GitHub)

### Example
```
Add CPU arch filter scheduler support

Explain what changed and why, wrapped at 72 characters. Bullets are ok.
```
